Amendment No. 3 to HB2359
Freeman
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2293* House Bill No. 2359
by deleting Section 4 and substituting:
SECTION 4. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 57-7-106(b)(3)(A), is amended by
deleting the subdivision and substituting:
(A)
(i) An applicant for a license as a retailer with a proposed retail location
that is within one thousand feet (1,000') of a private school, public school, or
charter school that serves any grade from kindergarten through grade twelve (K-
12) shall not sell HDCPs at such location unless the applicant provides the
commission with documentation that establishes that HDCPs were being offered
for sale at retail at such location on December 31, 2023.
(ii) Notwithstanding this chapter, a licensed retailer with a retail location
that is within one thousand feet (1,000') of a private school, public school, or
charter school that serves any grade from kindergarten through grade twelve (K-
12) shall not sell HDCP vapor products at such location.
SECTION 5. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 67, Chapter 4, Part 10, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
Notwithstanding this chapter, a vapor product retail dealer or retail vapor product
store with a retail location that is within one thousand feet (1,000') of a private school,
public school, or charter school that serves any grade from kindergarten through grade
twelve (K-12) shall not sell vapor products at such location.
SECTION 6.
HA1208
018254
- 1 -

(a) Section 4 and Section 5 of this act take effect July 1, 2027, the public welfare
requiring it, and applies to conduct occurring on or after that date.
(b) For all other purposes, this act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public
welfare requiring it.
